40|$|An {{electromagnetic}} wave (f = 9 GHz, Pi = 150 kW, τ = 1. 5 μs) is {{launched into a}} subcritical argon plasma (n e ≃ 1011 cm- 3, P 0 ≃ 5 × 10 - 4 Torr), resulting in a standing wave. The associated ponderomotive force generates an <b>ion</b> <b>acoustic</b> <b>wave</b> with a wave vector equal to twice the electromagnetic one and with a frequency satisfying the usual dispersion relation (fA ≃ 150 kHz). The main features of the <b>ion</b> <b>acoustic</b> <b>wave,</b> as measured in this 3 D experiment, agree with a simple theory. However, varying the plasma density, the <b>ion</b> <b>acoustic</b> spectrum reveals a non-linear feature, i. e. the existence of subharmonics...|$|R
